"""Google Play top-charts collector (best-effort) — the Android rank source.

WHY THIS EXISTS: flow anchors need (rank, observed_download_flow) pairs. Install
buckets give the flow, but the python google-play-scraper package has no
top-charts API, so nothing recorded Android ranks and anchors could never mint.
This module ports the request the JS google-play-scraper library uses
(facundoolano/google-play-scraper, MIT - lib/list.js): a POST to Play's
batchexecute endpoint (rpcid vyAe2) whose response embeds the chart list.

Best-effort by design: the endpoint is internal and may change or rate-limit.
Every failure returns [] (logged, never fatal) - a missed day just means fewer
anchors, never a crash and never fabricated ranks.
"""
